rdf:Description.lla:note: Registry of Indenture: 1871-01-13, Aberystwyth. It mentions in the Log Book for 1871-07-21 at Falmouth, that Alban fell from the masthead to the deck, fracturing his thigh bone and hurting his eye. A Dr. Guppy was called and A. was transferred to the 'Sailors Home Asylum' and left under the care of Dr. G. for further treatment.
A John Davies also mentioned in the Log Book as 'Mate'. No further information given.
Does not state what Thomas Williams does at the end of this voyage
